title: Unraveling Sums and Differences of Cubes

questions.question: Given $x^3+y^3=26$ and $x^2-xy+y^2=13$. Find the value of $x+y$.
Given $a^3-b^3=19$ and $a^2+ab+b^2=19$. Find the value of $a-b$.

questions.question: If $x^3+y^3=0$, then $(x+y)(x^2-xy+y^2)=0$. If $x \ne -y$, what can be inferred about $x^2-xy+y^2$?
If $a^3-b^3=0$, then $(a-b)(a^2+ab+b^2)=0$. If $a \ne b$, what can be inferred about $a^2+ab+b^2$?

questions.question: If $x+y=a$ and $xy=b$, express $x^3+y^3$ in terms of $a$ and $b$.
If $x-y=a$ and $xy=b$, express $x^3-y^3$ in terms of $a$ and $b$.
If $x^2+xy+y^2=A$ and $x-y=B$, find $x^3-y^3$ in terms of $A$ and $B$.
If $x^2-xy+y^2=C$ and $x+y=D$, find $x^3+y^3$ in terms of $C$ and $D$.
